
/* 'TOOLS/IMAGINATION.m' MODULE. Allows you to use the images from icons
   in your applications in a programmer friendly manner */
SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE!
SO THERE!
 ********************************************************************
 *           I M A G I N A T I O N   I N T E R F A C E              *
 *EXPORTED FUNCTIONS:                                               *
 *  init_imagination(), shutdown_imagination(),                     *
 *  main, other := disk_images(srcfile), pasteImage(image,x,y)      *
 ********************************************************************

init_imagination()
   initialises this module. Call once. Called by Muse, so if this module is
   used in a program using Muse, do not call this, and use the other functions
   AFTER muse has started up!

shutdown_imagination()
   close the module down. Do not call if you are using Muse!

main, other := disk_images(srcfile)
   Returns the two images pointed to by the icon indicated by srcfile which is a
   file name for and icon without the ".info" extension.

pasteImage(image,x,y)
   Splats the image provided into the standard rastport at location (x,y)

